pageContext.claim: “He [Biden] traveled from Delaware to a little tiny corner of Pennsylvania, like right next to Delaware, and he made a speech, and he said that he doesn't do these kind of rallies, because of COVID, you know, because of -- He doesn't do them because nobody shows up, that's why. Nobody shows up. COVID, COVID, COVID. It's all they talk about. The fake news. COVID, COVID, COVID.”
pageContext.analysis: Biden campaign rallies are purposely smaller because he and his surrogates are following federal guidelines designed to prevent the spread of the coronavirus; Trump consistently ignores the guidelines and puts his supporters at risk. Trump also wildly overestimates the size of his crowds.
